==English==
===Adverb===
'''less'''

#Not as much.
#:I have less tea than you have.
#:I have less tea than coffee.

====Usage note====
*'''Less''' is correctly used with uncountable nouns only. With plural nouns, the correct word is [[fewer]].  Many speakers and writers use [[less]] with plural nouns too, but this is considered to be incorrect.

====Antonym====
*[[more]]

====Translations====
*French: [[moins de]] ... [[que]]
*:I have less tea than you - ''J'ai moins de thé que toi''
*:I have less tea than coffee - ''J'ai moins de thé que de café'' 
*Italian: [[meno]] ... [[che]]
*:I have less tea than you - ''<to be checked>''
*:I have less tea than coffee - ''<to be checked>''